ces in the building  Library Cards To check out library materials  please present a VMI ID card  issued to all cadets during their first week and to faculty and staff by Human Resources upon request   or a library card  issued by circulation staff when any other patron registers  Renewals In person at the circulation desk By phone  464 7129 In response to an email overdue notice or by emailing circulation vmi edu Via My Library   My Library  This feature of the online catalog allows you to access your library record remotely  Circulation staff will be glad to demonstrate  You may see what you have borrowed  renew items  place holds  and update your contact information  Members of the VMI community use their usernames and passwords to log in Other patrons may set a PIN at the circulation desk  Holds and Recalls If an item you want is checked out by another patron  circulation staff will be happy to recall it and notify you when it is available  Help Finding Materials Circulation staff can provide a floor plan of the building and direct you to the materials you find in the library catalog They will search for materials which are not found in the correct location  Copies and Transparencies Copies are free for VMI cadets  faculty  and staff  This applies to both photocopies and micro copies  All other patrons are charged  0 10 per copy  plus tax  Circulation staff can make transparencies for  0 40 each  any time the library is open  Virginia sales tax is added to all payments made at the circulation desk   For questions concerning Circulation Services  contact Lt  Col  Susan Hastings at 464 7607 or hastingssf vmi edu  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 